Parameters in TextNG

1.What is the use of TestNG Parameters?
2.How to use the TestNG parameters?

TestNG Parameters : 100 testcases 
Prod url 
UAT url 
QA url 

Firefox browser
Chrome browser
Internet browser

Parameters can be passed at suite level and @ Test level
If a parameter is used for most of the test cases then we use scope parameters
The scope of the suite level  parameters is all the tests cases in the suite

The scope of the test level parameters only for the particular test case.

if you more than one parameter , then we need to pass the parameters in an array format
Parameters({"username","password"})

if suite level and test level parameters are same , then test level 
parameter will replace the suite level parameters

When you pass the parameters in XML , we need to run the tests using xml file,
if run the testNG class , then it thrown an error

Optional Parameters
1.How to use the testNG optional parameters?
2.How to pass the default value for a parameter in TestNG?

Optional parameters without passing the value , default value is consider as 
a optional parameters.

If the user passes the parameters then , user passed parameter 
will have highest priority

If user doesn't pass the parameter then ,optional parameter will be considered.


Note : We can execute the test cases in the order using XML file also 
but we have maintain the order of test cases.


























